comments.body:
Instead of making `_assetHandler` return a function, have you considered passing a closure here?
```dart
cascade = cascade.add((Request request) => _assetHandler(request, flutterProject));
```
and then, `_assetHandler` could look like this:
```dart
static Future<Response> _assetHandler(Request request, FlutterProject flutterProject) {
  if (request.url.path.contains('stack_trace_mapper')) {
    // ...
  }
  // ...
}
```

